U.K.’s Cameron Presses for Liberal Reform in Europe, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-24T01:56:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/u-k-s-cameron-presses-for-liberal-reform-in-europe-ft-says.html
U.K. Prime Minister  David Cameron ,
together with the leaders of eight other north European
countries, wrote to European Commission President Jose Manuel Barroso and European Union President  Herman Van Rompuy  urging
that other European countries accelerate their adoption of
liberal reforms such as the full opening of Europe’s services
market, the creation of a digital single economy and the
completion of the Doha trade round, the Financial Times
reported, citing the letter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 